    {
      "id": 209020,
      "postNumber": 1,
      "createdAt": "2024-11-07T08:58:12.860Z",
      "author": "Christoph (Christoph)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>It would be great to add emojis in view titles. I see this as an opportunity to better guide users visually. Also a picture can say more than a thousand words, so it would be possible to make very small but still understandable view titles, hence fitting more views in the view bar.</p>\n<p>Currently emojis are not working. You can add them, but after reloading the page, they are replaced by a question mark.</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 217327,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2025-01-14T17:10:28.992Z",
      "author": "cabanasr (Ruben Cabanas)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Same problem here. It’d be good to fix it. I use emojis to identify Boards and in a consolidated view I have emojis to quickly identify the tab. Unfortunately the “?” appear but not for all emojis! <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/gear.png?v=12\" title=\":gear:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":gear:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" />is fine for example</p>"
    },
